main event: On May 23, 1955, a civilian observer reported seeing a bright light in the sky, which was noted to have ten red lights in a circular formation and one white light in the center.
interesting points: The object was described as brighter than the brightest stars.,The observation lasted for five minutes.,The object was flying in a northeast direction.,The report indicates that it was possible to be an aircraft.,There are various fields included in the questionnaire related to conditions during the sighting.
sighted object: A light with ten red lights in a circular pattern and one white light in the center
